<div id="review_3538267956" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3538267956" />
    <a title="Mr. Caleb Benham" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/111111431-mr-caleb-benham"><img alt="Mr. Caleb Benham" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1598815691p2/111111431.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3538267956?book_show_action=true">Sep 08, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mr. Caleb Benham" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mr. Caleb Benham" href="/user/show/111111431-mr-caleb-benham">Mr. Caleb Benham</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9781598531237" href="/book/show/24940268-william-tecumseh-sherman">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3538267956" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5930077730789598142">William Tecumseh Sherman is considered by many military historians to be THE first modern general. An American legend who was as controversial as he was interesting; his life is central to understanding the United States as it is today. He was in California at the start of the 1849 gold rush, founded Louisiana State University, ensured Abraham&apos;s Lincoln&apos;s reelection in 1865, and was essential to the Union winning the Civil War. While not a writer by trade, General Sherman&apos;s memoirs are proof tha</span>
  <span id="freeText5930077730789598142" style="display:none">William Tecumseh Sherman is considered by many military historians to be THE first modern general. An American legend who was as controversial as he was interesting; his life is central to understanding the United States as it is today. He was in California at the start of the 1849 gold rush, founded Louisiana State University, ensured Abraham's Lincoln's reelection in 1865, and was essential to the Union winning the Civil War. While not a writer by trade, General Sherman's memoirs are proof that good writing not need to only come from those trained as authors; some of the best writing comes from those that lead interesting lives and in turn write about their own experiences. In my opinion, Sherman's memoirs are an essential part of understanding what it means to be American.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5930077730789598142" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

