<span id="freeTextContainer12015363053079240760">General Sherman was a man who knew how to put a sentence together. People often remember him only as the man who rode through Atlanta and left a trail of destruction behind him. They forget he was an educated man, who understood the concept of war and believed wholeheartedly in the cause of preserving the Union. He also was sworn to obey and to honor the office of the President of the United States. Sherman was an honorable man who had a tough role to play at a very disquieting time of American </span>
  <span id="freeText12015363053079240760" style="display:none">General Sherman was a man who knew how to put a sentence together. People often remember him only as the man who rode through Atlanta and left a trail of destruction behind him. They forget he was an educated man, who understood the concept of war and believed wholeheartedly in the cause of preserving the Union. He also was sworn to obey and to honor the office of the President of the United States. Sherman was an honorable man who had a tough role to play at a very disquieting time of American History.<br /><br />Huzzah!</span>
