<div id="review_3522000998" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3522000998" />
    <a title="Jeff Lacy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4833799-jeff-lacy"><img alt="Jeff Lacy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442632305p2/4833799.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3522000998?book_show_action=true">Sep 06, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeff Lacy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeff Lacy" href="/user/show/4833799-jeff-lacy">Jeff Lacy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3522000998" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1201105042750301414"><strong>A worthy memoir of a true patriot</strong><br/><br/>William Tecumseh Sherman’s memoir is worthy on so many levels: as an example of an illustrative and intelligent memoir; as a source for Civil War history, psychology into a commander leading an field army during war, and war or battle strategy and tactics. In the end though, at least I came away with a great admiration for General Sherman. His writing style is almost conversational. At least it is easy to read, warm, and very engaging. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

